HIS FATHER WAS THE LIBRARY CUSTODIAN AND THEY LIVED ABOVE THE LIBRARY
CLARK GREW UP FEELING SHAME THAT HIS FAMILY WAS POOR, BUT REALIZED THEY WERE RICH IN OTHER WAYS.
HE WOULD GO DOWN AND READ IN THE LIBRARY UNTIL 3 AM ANY TIME HE HAD QUESTIONS.
AS HE GREW UP, HE APPRECIATED HIS FAMILY AND HIS TIME SPENT READING.
HE WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GO TO COLLEGE.
HE WENT ON TO TEACH AT THE COLLEGE HE GRADUATED FROM.
HIS FATHER WAS VERY PROUD OF HIM.
